
// This Hyperlambda code checks if the value of the [rtl] node within [.arguments] is true. If it is, it updates the [.result] node by replacing occurrences of the string "[[rtl]]" with "true" using [strings.replace]. The [if] slot evaluates the condition, and if true, the [set-value] and [strings.replace] slots modify the [.result] node accordingly.
if:x:@.arguments/*/rtl
   set-value:x:@.result
      strings.replace:x:@.result
         .:[[rtl]]
         .:true
